Pre-Game Insights: Iceland comes into this game sitting in 3rd place in the group having picked up three points.
Iceland in the last game faced off against Turkey and they really struggled, scoring only a goal and conceding three.
Sverrir Ingi Ingason has returned to the team and needs to have a huge game.
Alfons Sampsted and Willum Thor Willumsson are both looking to move into the starting lineup and need to be strong.
Wales comes into this game sitting 2nd place in the group having picked up four points.
Wales faced off against Montenegro, scoring two goals and winning by a goal.
Joe Allen has returned from retirement and needs to have a strong game.
David Brooks, Nathan Broadhead, and Wes Burns have all been called up and need to be playmakers.
